, with Islam as a religion, and with Muhammad as a prophet, he must enter Paradise.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1884 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7425,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/02\/amnesty-mecca-liberated\/","url_meta":{"origin":39888,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Mercy: General amnesty the day Mecca is liberated","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 2, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: In the year of Mecca's liberation, Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib came to the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him, with Abu Sufyan ibn Harb and he embraced Islam. Al-Abbas said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, Abu Sufyan is a proud man, so give him something.\u201d The Prophet\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37960,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/07\/16\/by-hand-into-paradise\/","url_meta":{"origin":39888,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Jannah: The Prophet takes them by the hand into Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Munaydhir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever says when he awakens in the morning, \u2018I am pleased with Allah as a Lord, with Islam as a religion, and with Muhammad as a prophet,\u2019 then I am responsible for him and I will surely\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":16,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/09\/08\/calling-righteousness-sin\/","url_meta":{"origin":39888,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Guidance: Whoever calls others to righteousness or sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 8, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever calls to guidance will have a reward similar to those who follow him, without detracting from their rewards at all. Whoever calls to misguidance will have sin upon him similar to those who follow him, without\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/39888","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=39888"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-j